The institution says the situation has been contained and it has deployed additional security on campus. JOHANNESBURG The Tshwane University of Technology (TUT) says it is monitoring the situation at its Soshanguve campus following disruption of classes this week.The institution says the situation has been contained and it has deployed additional security at the campus to ensure the safety of students, staff and property.TUT s Willa de Ruyter says while academic activities continue on other TUT campuses, it s unclear why Soshanguve students are protesting. We are investigating the matter, it s not quite clear what caused the new disruptions because there was an agreement that activities would continue. &quot;Last week, during the memorial service for Benjamin Phehla students publicly declared that they would go back to class in honour of Benjamin. 